SADC Moves to Fight Border Crimes
LUSAKA , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Immigration and customs officials from members of the Southern African Development Community ( SADC ) met here Thursday to harmonize legislation on border controls to effectively fight borders crimes .
The problems concerning the operations of the immigration and customs and excise in the region will also be addressed at the two-day meeting .
Francis Ndhlovu , Zambian Inspector-General of Police , told the meeting that with the prevailing cases of forged travel documents , drug trafficking and smuggling remain a source of concern .
Ndhlovu expressed his hope that the frequent meetings of the immigration and customs officials will facilitate increased cooperation in trade , boost tourism and ease the movement of the people in the region .
